<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-12-05"><hi rend="italic">December 5,
                                1889</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 22.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 49, of the 14th
                            ultimo, in which you inclose copy of your note urging upon the Peruvian
                            Government the payment of the claim of certain American citizens who had
                            served that Government as members of the Hydrographic Commission in the
                            survey of the Amazon and its tributaries.</p>
                        <p>Your action is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>